   DNA-SOLVING-CRIMES (Chicago) _ In a novel legal gambit that
stretches the law to match the developing science of DNA, a
prosecutor in Wisconsin has filed rape and kidnapping charges
against a defendant who has no name. John Doe is known only by his
DNA code, extracted from semen samples from three rapes, samples
which have been tested after six years of storage in a police
property room. By Bill Dedman.
</P>
