   BUSH-CAMPAIGN-ASSESS (Washington) _ These are uncomfortable days
for Republicans on Capitol Hill. Once again they are locked in a
chaotic, down-to-the-wire budget battle with President Clinton.
They have been forced into a debate over managed health care that
offends the anti-regulatory sensibilities of many Republicans. And
now the party's front-running presidential candidate seems to be
defining his own credentials as a ``compassionate conservative'' by
distancing himself from them. By Alison Mitchell.
