starting to be embraced by the mainstream as they evolve into more
subtle forms for companies to promote products at the grass-roots
level. The purpose, companies say, is mainly to reach younger
consumers by cutting past all the static that the companies
themselves created and that young people have tuned out _
television, radio, print and Internet ads. By Constance L. Hays.
</P>
<P>
   MARKETPLACE-DIVIDENDS (Undated) _ If the measure of corporate
America's financial health is its ability and willingness to
increase dividends to shareholders, then you might think the
country is in a recession. Standard &AMP; Poor's Corp. reports that 117
companies announced dividend increases in September, 10 fewer than
had raised their payouts a year earlier. What is unusual is that
the economy is doing so well even while companies are growing more
reluctant to raise their dividends. By Floyd Norris.
