<P>
   SCIENCE-MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   CDC-FLU _ As the flu season looms, CDC will announce what
strains are likely to circulate this year and urge at-risk people
to get their immunizations. (Kim, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
15.
</P>
<P>
   SYPHILIS _ Rates of syphilis are at an alltime low in the US,
meaning that the disease - which can cause disability, death, and
birth defects if untretaed - is within reach of being eliminated in
the US. Less than 30 counties remain reservoirs of the disease, and
Fulton (Atlanta) is one - even though rates have been falling in
Fulton and in Georgia, Fulton remains one of the 10 worst in the
country. Immediate action is needed, because syphilis swings in
10-year cycles, and the peak of the last epidemic was 9 years ago.
(McKenna, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   SYPHILIS-PROGRESS _ Surgeon General David Satcher and CDC
Director Jeffrey Koplan announce in Nashville a community-oriented
national push to eliminate syphilis. Story will at least address
their national plan; we hope also to get details of what the feds
have funded in Georgia and Fulton Co., and perhaps even to go to a
clinic that treats STDs. (McKenna, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
15.
</P>
