   TRAVEL-GETAWAY _ Portsmouth Village, the loneliest and most
haunting place on North Carolina's Outer Banks is nestled on the
northern tip of 22-mile-long Portsmouth Island, the Village once
vied with Ocracoke as the largest settlement on the Outer Banks.
Established by the General Assembly in 1753, it grew to thrive in
the 1800s as a storage and support center for the shipping
industry. Boats that couldn't navigate the shallow Pamlico Sound
would off-load their cargo onto flat draft boats at Portsmouth.
(Teater, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 35.
</P>
<P>
   BAHAMAS _ The calm after the storm. Hurricane Floyd slammed
smack into the Bahamas, but many islands have been recoving
quickly. (Blackerby, Palm Beach Post) WITH PHOTOS.
