<P>
   SOUTH-POLE-RESCUE (Albany, N.Y.) _ An Air National Guard crew
from this area, now on its way to the South Pole, will try to make
an unprecedented landing there next week, braving extreme weather
conditions to evacuate a 47-year-old ailing physician who
discovered a lump in her breast earlier this year. By LINDA
TRISCHITTA.
</P>
<P>
   MEDICINE-GRANT (Berkeley, Calif) _ The University of California
at Berkeley has received $50 million, its largest gift ever, to
help construct one of two new buildings for a program to bring
together physical and biological scientists in pursuit of medical
innovations. By ULYSSES TORASSA.
</P>
<P>
   PLASTIC-SURGEON (Oakland, Calif.) _ Plastic surgeon John Emery
testifies here about how his once-flourishing practice has dwindled
_ after the mysterious post-operative death of a facelift patient _
to the point where he now wants to close his clinic and become what
he calls a ``country doctor.'' His clinic pioneered outpatient
cosmetic surgery in Northern California. By ELIZABETH FERNANDEZ.
</P>
<P>
   POLICE-D.A. (San Francisco) _ More than 98 percent of San
Francisco police officers have voted in favor of ousting District
Attorney Terence Hallinan and replacing him with former prosecutor
Bill Fazio in the Nov. 3 election. By JIM HERRON ZAMORA.
</P>
