</P>
<P>
   BEST-FOOD (San Francisco) _ They'll drive more than 50 miles for
some silky foie gras. They want a fine wine, not fries, with that.
They don't necessarily make more money than other people, but they
spend more on food. They think San Francisco is an absolutely
fabulous restaurant town _ the nation's best, even better than
runner-up New York City. These are among the key findings in a new
nationwide study. By DAVID ARMSTRONG.
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-COLUMN (Houston) _ A reader asks, ``I moved to Humble
