<HEADLINE>
DANITRA VANCE BROKE GROUND ON `SNL'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Danitra Vance was one of the deceased ``Saturday Night Live''
cast members honored during the 25th anniversary TV special. When
was she on the show?
</P>
<P>
   _ A.K., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: Vance, the first African-American woman to become a
``Saturday Night Live'' cast member, appeared during the 1985-86
season.
</P>
<P>
   Some of the recurring characters she portrayed that season were
Cicely Tyson; ``That Black Girl''; and Cabrini Green Harlem Watts
Jackson, according to the ``Saturday Night Live'' frequently asked
questions list compiled by fans on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   A Chicago native, Vance was a performance artist who was a
Second City member before joining ``Saturday Night Live.'' She won
two Dramalogue awards for her stage performances in ``The Colored
Museum'' and ``Spunk.''
</P>
<P>
   After her breast cancer was diagnosed, Vance incorporated her
experiences into a solo performance, ``The Radical Girl's Guide to
Radical Mastectomy.'' She died in 1994 at age 35.
</P>
<P>
   The ``Saturday Night Live'' FAQ is available on the Web at
www.faqs.org/faqs/tv/sat-night-live.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How much are daytime soap actors paid if they have active
story lines?
</P>
<P>
   _ E.C., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The most popular actors on soaps can earn $5,000 to $7,000
per episode in which they appear, according to TV Guide soap
reporter Michael J. Maloney.
</P>
<P>
   ``Newcomers make between $950 and $1,300 an episode with a
guarantee of one and a half appearances per week,'' Maloney
reported on the TV Guide Web site (www.tvguide.com). A popular
actor may appear as often as four times a week.
</P>
<P>
   ``Seasoned players who aren't megastars but have been around for
five years or so earn $2,000 to $3,000 per show,'' he wrote.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to James Morrison, who played T.C. McQueen
on ``Space: Above and Beyond?''
</P>
<P>
   _ J.T.S., Dover, Ohio
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Morrison in care of Judy Schoen and Associates, 606
N. Larchmont, Suite 309, Los Angeles, CA 90004.
</P>
<P>
   The 45-year-old actor made appearances this year in the films
``Abilene'' and ``Shadow of Doubt'' and episodes of ``Becker'' and
``Nash Bridges.''
</P>
<P>
   In March, Morrison and his wife, Riad Galayini, had a son,
Seamus. Fans of the actor have published an extensive Web site at
www.lifeofanactor.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
