   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-SENATE (Washington) _ First Lady Hillary Rodham Clinton
files a statement of candidacy for the U.S. Senate from New York
with the secretary of the Senate and the Federal Election
Commission. The action sets the stage for a fundraising blitz by
Mrs. Clinton later this month after she returns from Europe. By
STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   GORE-SMOG (New York) _ Vice President Al Gore squarely blames
Texas Gov. George W. Bush for the worsening smog conditions in
Houston. Groups that monitor ozone levels say has the Texas city
has replaced Los Angeles as the nation's smog capital. By ALAN
BERNSTEIN.
