</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush's bold
move to capture the middle and distance himself from conservative
congressional Republicans is a clever long-range strategy. In the
short run, however, he's got trouble. Republicans complain he is
hurting their campaign to keep control of the House next year. And
by running a general election campaign now, he is counting his
chickens before the eggs are hatched. By MARIANNE MEANS.
