May 1 open-wheel race at Lowe's Motor Speedway in Charlotte have
been interviewed by the FBI, and track officials are increasing
security for Sunday's NASCAR race after a rash of bombings and bomb
threats at Lowe's stores near Charlotte. The FBI is trying to
determine if there is a link between the bombings and the deaths of
three spectators who were killed at the speedway.
(Schlabach/Carvell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 28.
