<P>
   FBC-QUINCYCARTER _ UGA Quarterback Quincy Carter, touted before
the season as a Heisman Trophy candidate, may not even be an
All-SEC selection at season's end. He is having an ordinary year,
but Georgia coach Jim Donnan says that shouldn't be a rap against
the sophomore. Donnan says the Bulldogs can't be just ``The Quincy
Carter Show'' and be successful. (Towers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-WARRICKARREST _ Florida State's Peter Warrick is arrested on
grand theft charges in connection with a clothing purchase at a
department store in Tallahassee. So is teammate and roommate
Laveranues Coles. Both were suspended from playing in Saturday's
game against Miami and could be suspended for the season.
(Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER
</P>
<P>
   SOC-CROWDS _ Crowds at women's soccer games are hitting all-time
highs this year. By its sixth game, Georgia had exceeded last
season's attendance. North Carolina is experiencing the same, as
are other schools. Georgia coach Bill Barker credits not only the
summer's World Cup but the ``family atmosphere'' at games. (Parker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
