   FRANKEL-INDICT (Undated) _ Fugitive financier Martin Frankel,
who fled the United States and is now in a German prison, was
indicted by a federal grand jury Thursday on 36 counts of fraud,
money-laundering and racketeering in a scheme that siphoned over
$200 million from a group of Southern insurance companies and used
the money for his own benefit. By Leslie Wayne.
