   SWEATSHOPS (Undated) _ Discussions between manufacturers and
advocates for the rights of overseas workers. By Steven Greenhouse.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Bottom)
</P>
<P>
   REVLON-NORRIS-COLUMN (Undated) _ To hear George Fellows, the
Revlon president, tell it, everything is going great at Revlon Inc.
But in the week since Revlon disclosed an inventory problem, its
stock has plunged 41 percent, to $10.75, even after bouncing back
$2 Thursday. The prices of Revlon junk bonds have also fallen
sharply. It is not easy to tell whether Fellow's optimism _ he
forecasts that the company will have positive operating cash flow
next year _ is justified. But it is clear that Revlon's near-term
prospects hinge on the kindness of the banks that have lent the
company lots of money. By Floyd Norris.
</P>
<P>
   (With graphic.)
</P>
