<P>
   &QL; 
CHINESE (Washington) - Two officials of the Chinese embassy here
have warned congressional investigators that their probe of the
corporation that owns the Chinese Cultural Center in Phoenix could
damage economic and political ties between the two countries. The
warning was presented at a Capitol Hill meeting last month to
investigators at the House Committee on Government Reform. The
Chinese officials were Shi Jianxin, the embassy's top trade
official, and Ci Bin, the embassy's First Secretary.
</P>
<P>
   Committee Chairman Dan Burton, R-Indiana, on Thursday said the
warning heightened his interest in pursuing the investigation of
COFCO a giant agricultural import and export corporation owned by
the Chinese government. By JERRY KAMMER. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
NTSB (Phoenix) - An in-flight accident that injured four America
West flight attendants was caused by a faulty warning system that
had ongoing problems for months that had not been corrected,
according to the NTSB's lead investigator. The federal agency is
looking at why problems persisted with the ground proximity warning
system. The pilots, reacting to a false warning, pulled the nose of
the plane up suddenly and hit maximum thrust, resulting in serious
injuries to two flight attendants and minor injuries to two others.
By PETER CORBETT. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``F''
categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
FORTIER (Phoenix) - So how deeply involved was Kingman, Ariz.'s
</P>
<P>
   Michael Fortier in the planning for the Oklahoma City bombing?
The government always contended that he was heavily involved since
Timothy McVeigh had detailed his plans to him for the bombing and
Fortier was with McVeigh when he stopped off in Oklahoma City
months before the bombing to case out the Murrah Federal Building.
But there's a school of thought now that Fortier wasn't really
involved at all and that he should be freed from prison now after
serving four years. The thinking is that McVeigh gave weapons to
Fortier for sale not for his help in the bomb plot but to pay back
rent for all the time that McVeigh mooched off him. Fortier may be
released on Friday. By MARK SHAFFER. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
