<P>
   ICE-WARMING (Seattle) _ One catastrophic potential effect of
global warming is the predicted rise in worldwide sea levels by 15
to 20 feet should the massive West Antarctic Ice Sheet melt and
flood the planet's densely populated coastal areas. But scientists
at the University of Washington have determined the melt-down is
already happening and it's not because of global warming.
</P>
<P>
   By Tom Paulson. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BOMBER-VETS (Seattle) _ They survived the hellish skies over
Nazi-occupied Europe nearly six decades ago, bombing German targets
with the state-of-the-art B-17 Flying Fortress. For the men of the
94th Bomb Group, 8th Air Force, the ensuing years have failed to
weaken the strong ties and deep friendships forged in war as the
veterans would meet every two years to share memories, laughter and
tears. Until now. By mutual agreement, the aging veterans are
holding their final reunion in Seattle this week, the city that
built their sturdy planes.
</P>
<P>
   By Ed Offley. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
