there's little logical resolution to this talky, slow and
unsatisfying film that purports to delve into how people respond to
tragedy and the ghosts that result. Harrison Ford and Kristin Scott
Thomas are the grieving souls who bond after they discover their
spouses were having an affair. The film meanders and has huge gaps
of logic and everyone seems to be moving on slow speed.
</P>
