<P>
   (NYT47) NEW YORK -- Oct. 7, 1999 -- NY-CLINTON, 10-07 --
President Clinton shaking hands with James P. Hoffa, general
president of the International Brotherhood of Teamsters, before
Clinton delivered an address during a dinner honoring Hoffa
Thursday night. The meeting was the first time a president had
appeared so publicly with the teamsters since President Franklin D.
Roosevelt spoke at one of its annual conventions 50 years ago.
(James Estrin/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT46) CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- Oct. 7, 1999 -- NYTIMES-COLUMNIST,
10-07 -- The New York Times announced Thursday that Paul Krugman,
an economics professor at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology
and an author known for his theories on international trade and
economics, would become a columnist on the Op-Ed page. Krugman's
column will appear twice a week, beginning in January, and will be
The Times' first regular Op-Ed column devoted to economics,
business and finance. (Michael Quan/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT45) UNDATED -- Oct. 7, 1999 -- SUB-CREAM-PUFFS-LADN, 10-07
-- A dessert menu mainstay for 10 years at Chaya Brasserie in Los
Angeles is this Pistachio Ice Cream Profiteroles With Hot Fudge and
Cinnamon Biscotti. Designed by the French-trained executive chef,
the creation ($7.50), which is topped with a sugar-cookie flower
design and a chocolate cookie cone is one of the three most popular
from among the 12 desserts offered nightly. (Charlotte
Schmid-Maybach/Los Angeles Daily News)
</P>
