<P>
   (NYT18) GAINESVILLE, Fla. -- Oct. 7, 1999 -- TEACHING-SCULPTURE,
10-07 -- More than a decade ago, Duane Ellifritt, a University of
Florida civil engineering professor, constructed a 14-foot high
teaching sculpture that shows how pieces of steel can be shaped and
connected. In the 13 years since, almost 100 universities have
copied his idea. On Thursday, the University of Florida honored the
original. ``I'm surprised no one ever thought of it before I did,''
says Ellifritt, 64. (Dede Smith/Gainesville Sun Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) NEW YORK -- Oct. 7, 1999 -- CONTACT-THEATER-REVIEW-2,
10-07 -- Deborah Yates and Boyd Gaines in ``Contact,'' which opened
Thursday night at the Mitzi E. Newhouse Theater. The production,
choreographed and directed by Susan Stroman and written by John
Weidman, is a sustained endorphin rush of an evening, that rare
entertainment that has you floating all the way home. (Sara
Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) NEW YORK -- Oct. 7, 1999 -- CONTACT-THEATER-REVIEW-1,
10-07 -- ``Contact,'' choreographed and directed by Susan Stroman
and written by John Weidman, opened Thursday night at the Mitzi E.
