Martin Hingston and, at rear, Boyd Gaines. This new musical throbs
with wit, sex appeal and a perfectionist's polish. (Sara
Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) NEAR CRAWFORD NOTCH, N.H. -- Oct. 7, 1999 --
NEWENGLAND-FOLLIAGE-BOS-FLOATER -- Thursday's crisp autumn air in
much of New England made it the perfect time for the area's
seasonal ``leaf peepers'' to take a ride on The Conway Scenic
Railroad. The railroad, which runs through the White Mountains,
allows riders to enjoy the changing foliage while traveling back
and froth from North Conway to Crawford Notch. (Mark Wilson/Boston
Globe Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) NEW YORK -- Oct. 7, 1999 -- NIH-SLOAN, 10-07 -- Dr.
