</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) TRENTON, N.J. -- Oct. 7, 1999 -- TRAFFIC-DELAYS, 10-07
-- Widening Route 29 near Trenton is expected to save an average
commuter 25 hours a year, but is causing 80 hours in delays. Thus,
the break-even point - the date at which the Trenton commuter
recoups the time lost because of the construction - will come in
2012. (Laura Pedrick/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) NEW YORK -- Oct. 7, 1999 -- LESBIAN-COPS, 10-07 --
Police Officers Elizabeth Bryant, seated, and Marilyn Trapanotto at
home in Brooklyn. Ms. Bryant, claiming her civil rights were
violated, has brought a $5 million lawsuit against the city, the
department, three officers and Commissioner Howard Safir. ``Not
only did the Police Department turn their backs on her, they
punished her for coming forward,'' says her lawyer, Joseph
Tacopina. (Librado Romero/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT10) NEW YORK -- Oct. 7, 1999 -- THEATER-NOTES, 10-07 -- Amy
Sedaris in ``The Country Club'' at the Greenwich House Theater.
First, she acts. Then, every night after the show, she helps to
sell her homemade vanilla cupcakes in the lobby. ``It's great,''
Ms. Sedaris says. ``And I go home with 25 bucks in my pocket.''
(Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) UNDATED -- Oct. 7, 1999 -- TANDEM-BIKES-B&AMP;W, 10-07 --
Participants in an annual Tandem Weekend ride, starting in
Millville, N.J., and covering more than 50 miles. A good road
tandem bike starts at more than $2,000, and the best models run
$5,000 or more. (Allen St. John/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT8) WORCESTER, Mass. -- Oct. 7, 1999 --
ONLINE-RETAILERS-ART-BOS, 10-07 -- From left, John Burke, director
of network and operations for toysmart.com; Wayne Teres, toysmart's
director of logistics and Devdutt Yellurkar, chief executive of
Yantra Corp., in toysmart.com's warehouse. ``People try a Web site
once, and if they have a problem, they never come back,'' said
Yellurkar, whose company helps Web sites such as toysmart.com
